#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:1
msgid "Macros and Attributes"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:3
msgid "Sort attributes and derive traits alphabetically (`alphabetical-attrs`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:5
msgid ""
"When an item carries multiple outer attributes, list non-derive attributes "
"in **alphabetical order** by name and place `#[derive(...)]` **last**. "
"Within `#[derive(...)]`, list the traits **alphabetically** as well."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:12
msgid ""
"// Good — non-derive attributes sorted; derive is last with sorted traits\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:13
#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:20
msgid "\"alloc\""
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:17
msgid "// Bad — arbitrary ordering\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:25
msgid ""
"Placing `#[derive(...)]` last ensures that derive macros always see the item "
"after all attribute macros (e.g., `#[padding_struct]`, `#[pod_union]`) have "
"transformed it. Derive helper attributes (e.g., `#[serde(...)]`, "
"`#[clap(...)]`) stay immediately after `#[derive(...)]`. Sorting the "
"remaining attributes alphabetically eliminates hesitation over placement and "
"reduces noise in diffs."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:37
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#3080](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/"
"pull/3080#discussion_r3031834321) (motivating discussion) and PR [\\#2898]"
"(https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2898#discussion_r2763969731) "
"(earlier ad-hoc ordering choice)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:43
msgid "Use `#[expect(dead_code)]` with restraint (`expect-dead-code`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:45
msgid ""
"In general, dead code should be avoided because _(i)_ it introduces "
"unnecessary maintenance overhead, and _(ii)_ its correctness can only be "
"guaranteed by manual and error-prone review."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:50
msgid "Dead code is acceptable only when all of these hold:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:52
msgid ""
"A _concrete case_ will be implemented in the future that turns the dead code "
"into used code."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:54
msgid "The semantics are _clear_ enough, even without the use case."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:56
msgid ""
"The dead code is _simple_ enough that both the committer and the reviewer "
"can be confident it is correct without testing."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:59
msgid "It serves as a counterpart to existing non-dead code."
msgstr "它与现有的非死代码相对应。"

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:61
msgid ""
"For example, it is fine to add ABI constants that are unused because the "
"corresponding feature is partially implemented."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:65
msgid ""
"See also: [Rust Reference: Diagnostic attributes](https://doc.rust-lang.org/"
"reference/attributes/diagnostics.html) and rustc "
"[`unfulfilled_lint_expectations`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/rustc/lints/"
"listing/warn-by-default.html#unfulfilled-lint-expectations)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:69
msgid "Suppress lints at the narrowest scope (`narrow-lint-suppression`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:71
msgid ""
"When suppressing lints, the suppression should affect as little scope as "
"possible. This makes readers aware of the exact places where the lint is "
"generated and makes it easier for subsequent committers to maintain the "
"suppression."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:79
msgid "// Good — each method is individually marked\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:89
msgid "// Bad — the entire trait is suppressed\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:95
msgid ""
"There is one exception: if it is clear enough that every member will trigger "
"the lint, it is reasonable to expect the lint at the type level."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:108
msgid ""
"See also: [Clippy `allow_attributes`](https://rust-lang.github.io/rust-"
"clippy/master/#allow_attributes), [Clippy `allow_attributes_without_reason`]"
"(https://rust-lang.github.io/rust-clippy/master/"
"#allow_attributes_without_reason), and rustc "
"[`unfulfilled_lint_expectations`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/rustc/lints/"
"listing/warn-by-default.html#unfulfilled-lint-expectations)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:113
msgid "Prefer functions over macros (`macros-as-last-resort`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:115
msgid ""
"Prefer functions and generics over macros. Macros are powerful but harder to "
"understand, debug, test, and format. Reach for a macro only when the type "
"system or generics cannot express what you need (e.g., variadic arguments, "
"compile-time code generation, or DSL syntax)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:125
msgid "// Good — a generic function covers all types\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:130
msgid "// Bad — a macro where a function would suffice\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/macros-and-attributes.md:139
msgid ""
"See also: _The Rust Programming Language_, Chapter 20.5 \"Macros\"; [Rust by "
"Example: Macros](https://doc.rust-lang.org/rust-by-example/macros.html)."
msgstr ""
